question.value:
Outcome Variables: Participants will rank six communication methods (Face to Face, Phone call, Letter, Email, Text/Whatsapp, Online/instant messaging) in their preferred order, for seven different scenarios. This will create seven outcome variables; 1) Ranked communication preferences for accessing services; 2) Ranked communication preferences for customer support; 3) Ranked communication preferences for work; 4) Ranked communication preferences for school/college/University; 5) Ranked communication preferences for participating in research; 6) Ranked communication preferences for contacting friends; 7) Ranked communication preferences for contacting family. 

Predictor Variables: 1) Participant Age - this will be measured via a self report demographic questionnaire; 2) Self reported age at diagnosis - this will be measured via a self report demographic questionnaire; 3) Anxiety levels - this will be measured using the General Anxiety Disorder-7 questionnaire (GAD-7, Spitzer, Kroenke, Williams, &amp; Löwe, 2006); 
4) Camouflaging behaviours - this will be measured using the Camouflaging Autistic Traits Questionnaire (CAT-Q, Hull et al., 2019).

