There are 3 conditions: 

1) a "neutral" condition in which participants receive no additional information about the reviewer's relationship to the bakery that's being reviewed;
2) a "friend" condition in which participants are told that the reviewer is good friends with the owner of the bakery;
3) a "rival" condition in which participants are told that the owner of the bakery is a rival of the reviewer

